Package: bayesGDS
Type: Package
Title: Braun and Damien algorithm for Scalable Rejection Sampling
Version: 0.6.0.9990
Date: 2015-02-09
Authors@R: person(family="Braun", given="Michael", role=c("aut","cre","cph"), email="braunm@smu.edu")
URL: coxprofs.cox.smu.edu/braunm
Description: This package contains functions to help users implement the Generalized Direct Sampling algorithm for Bayesian hierarchical models (Braun and Damien, 2015). GDS is useful for sampling from posterior distributions for which there is a large number of conditionally independent heterogeneous units.
License: MPL (== 2.0)
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2),
	 Matrix (>= 1.1.5),
	 compiler
Suggests: sparseHessianFD(>= 0.2.0),
	  sparseMVN(>= 0.2.0),
	  mvtnorm,
       	  trustOptim (>= 0.8.5),
	  plyr (>= 1.8),
	  ggplot2,
	  dplyr,
	  tidyr,
  	  testthat,
	  knitr
Roxygen: list(wrap=TRUE)
